## Copy Quality Test

A string passes only if ALL five answer YES. Any NO → rewrite before shipping.

1. [Binary question specific to this product — e.g. "Does this copy mention at least one personal element (mệnh, Dụng Thần, tuổi, Can Chi) — or is this an ambient/background screen that doesn't require personalization?"]
2. [Binary question — e.g. "If read aloud, does it sound like a [age] year old [city] person talking to family — not like a translated text or system notification?"]
3. [Binary question — e.g. "Does it end with an action or specific information the user can use immediately — not a sales pitch or open-ended question?"]
4. [Binary question — e.g. "Is it free of every word in the Forbidden Words and Forbidden Opening Words lists?"]
5. [Binary question — e.g. "If the user just paid credits to see this, does it feel like the question in their head has been answered — not explained at length or followed by more questions?"]

## Hard Rules

These apply regardless of the per-project voice and tone above.

- All UI text uses real data variables — never lorem ipsum or placeholder strings
- Copy slots defined in wireframe metadata must be populated before committing
- Dynamic values use actual variable names: `{{user.display_name}}`, `{{item.title}}`
- Error messages: state what failed + why + what to do next — three parts, one sentence
- Copy written in [language] for [market] — follow locale conventions for punctuation, number formatting, and currency
